{"actual_usd":0.125845,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":234,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24467,"reply":"\"I don't think you'd get one clean, tidy reel, if that's what you're asking.\" *I hook a flour-dusted thumb into my apron and glance toward the bakery window, where the light's gone bright on the sill.* \"You'd have seen a stone already moved. Grave clothes left behind. Women arriving in grief and then jolted clear through by angels and by the fact that the tomb was empty. Mary lingering, weeping, then realizing the man speaking to her was Jesus himself. Later, others seeing him alive with their own eyes.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through carefully.* \"What you would not have gotten, far as the stories tell it, is a cameraman standing inside the tomb catching the exact instant of resurrection like a stage trick. The gospels give you the aftermath first, then the appearances. Which, honestly, feels more like real life to me. God often leaves you with witnesses and an empty place where death was supposed to keep its grip.\"\n\n\"Are you asking because you want the sequence plain, or because you’re trying to figure out whether the whole thing sounds trustworthy?\"","rolling_24h_usd":72.21068499999997,"run_id":"2522a674-db97-460c-966a-2cbc5c424aec"}
